headline: What Is Shaping The Next Chapter In The Keysight Technologies (KEYS) Story Today
summary: Keysight Technologies just saw its modeled fair value edge up from US$220.00 to about US$220.69 as recent Street commentary absorbed better than expected earnings delivery, steady margins, and signs of demand stabilization. Analysts who raised their targets often cited fiscal Q4 EPS above consensus, guidance for fiscal Q1 EPS ahead of expectations, and early signs that wireless and defense demand may be firming. More cautious voices still referenced cyclicality and a steady 5% to 7% organic...

headline: Does Keysight’s New SOS Enterprise Platform Reshape the AI Software Narrative for Keysight Technologies (KEYS)?
summary: In early February 2026, Keysight Technologies launched SOS Enterprise, an advanced engineering data management platform that automates governance, traceability, and compliance to help semiconductor and electronics organizations prepare their design data for AI adoption at scale across multiple sites. By turning fragmented engineering information into a single, governed system of record with versioned, traceable assets, SOS Enterprise directly targets one of the biggest obstacles to deploying...
